IMG_5022-EDIT1900×1614 431 KB

Does anyone recognize what brand of CNC this is? We inherited it when we moved into our new shop space. It originally was at another school, then moved to our school. When the previous occupants of our new shop space moved to the new tech school they left it behind, and told us it didn’t work, but we could have it if we wanted. It’s apparently missing some parts, but we think we can get it working again. Being able to go to the manufacturer’s web page will help.

We looked everywhere on it and can’t find a brand name. A reverse image search didn’t give us any hints either. It has a 5’ square bed.

Does anyone have an inkling of what it might be? Thanks!

IMHO you should think of this thing as a pile of parts that might be useful to make a DIY tool. And for most FRC teams, a DIY CNC is not a good idea, because it’s more work than the students or most mentors have time for. If you want that, though, go for it!

Another thing about this machine is that it will be marginal for aluminum, due to its low stiffness and low power. I have a similar machine at home: v-wheels, extruded rails, router spindle, and it chatters and cuts slowly. Accuracy may be marginal as well, depending on what you’re trying to do. This style of machine is really intended for woodworking.
